Documentary following groups of 4, 5 and 6 year olds as they learn to navigate the world around them. JOHANNESBURG - A clip featuring the adorable cast of The Secret Life of 4, 5 and 6-Year Olds has gone viral on social media. The show has been described as a documentary following groups of 4, 5 and 6-year-olds who are learning to navigate the world around them. READ: Should parents ask their children to apologise? In the short clip, a group of young girls and boys can be seen getting excited and trying to talk to each other through a window. Many social media users have described the interaction between the kids as adorable and said they would become followers of the show after watching the clip.